        Google's Agent2Agent (A2A) and Anthropic's Model Context Protocol (MCP) are the two dominant
        open protocols shaping the AI agent ecosystem. They are frequently compared as competitors.
        They are not — they solve fundamentally different problems. MCP connects agents to tools.
        A2A connects agents to agents. Understanding that distinction determines everything about
        which one your project needs, and whether you need both.
      </p>
